---
import Marquee from "@/components/lib/marquee.svelte";
---

<style>
  p {
    margin-block: 0.5rem;
  }
  .note {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    /* font-style: italic; */
    background-color: #ffffff20;
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
    margin-left: 2rem;
    padding: 0.25rem;
    border: 0.2rem solid;
    border-color: var(--border-extrude);
  }
</style>

<h1>Welcome!!</h1>
<p>
  This is my 3rd itteration of this site! I recreated this on a whim after
  finding out about Astro 🚀, and opted to use React ⚛️ and Svelte 🇸 (and Vite
  ⚡ as it comes bundled with astro) for interactivity!<br />If that makes no
  sense to you, thats fair - this is basically word soup icl
</p>

<div class="wrapper" style="--overflow: 0.5rem">
  <Marquee
    images={[
      {
        src: "/logos/astro.svg",
        alt: "astro logo",
        url: "https://astro.build",
        accent: "#D83333",
      },
      {
        src: "/logos/svelte.svg",
        alt: "svelte logo",
        url: "https://svelte.dev",
        accent: "#FF3E00",
      },
      {
        src: "/logos/react.svg",
        alt: "react logo",
        url: "https://reactjs.org",
        accent: "#00D8FF",
      },
      {
        src: "/logos/vite.svg",
        alt: "vite logo",
        url: "https://vitejs.dev",
        accent: "#41D1FF",
      },
    ]}
  />
</div>
<p>
  This site is designed like windows 95 🪟 and the windows drag, so go check em
  out!!
</p>
<p>
  Heres a list of features i added or improved:
  <ol>
    <li>It works <b>on mobile</b>!!! ☎️</li>
    <li>A debug page which makes accessing debug 🪲 items much easier</li>
    <li>
      The UI can be scaled 🔍 via settings, via browser zoom, or via a custom
      default font size!
      <div class="note">
        (note that this site is designed on a 100% zoom, 100% scale, 16pt
        default font size on a 24" 1920x1080 screen with a ~600x900 viewport
        size (small viewport bc terminal, pip, and dev tools))
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>Theres license information! 📜</li>
    <li>
      Vibrant debug logs
      <details class="note">
        <summary>For Mobile Users:</summary>
        If youre a mobile user and want to try look at the debug logs, heres a nifty
        tool to add dev tools to your current page: <a
          href="https://github.com/liriliri/eruda">Eruda</a
        >
        <br />
        Note that I couldnt make it work with the instructions they provided, so
        I made a userscript which runs it on every page! Click <button
          onclick={`// ==UserScript==
// @name         Eruda - Mobile devtools
// @namespace    http://tampermonkey.net/
// @version      2024-09-26
// @description  Loads Eruda dev tools on every site
// @author       Liriliri (Script created by afterlifepro)
// @match        https://github.com/liriliri/eruda
// ==/UserScript==

(function() {
    'use strict';

    // Your code here...
    javascript:(function () { var script = document.createElement('script'); script.src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/eruda"; document.body.append(script); script.onload = function () { eruda.init(); } })(); // eslint-expect-error
})();`}
          class="link">here</button
        > to copy the code so that you can paste it into a new script! (look up a
        guide on how to make new scripts if you need to)
      </details>
    </li>
    <li>Improved how new apps are created as a developer 🤖</li>
    <li>More will come soon!!!!</li>
  </ol>
</p>

<p>
  Heres a list of features I plan to add at some point:
  <ul>
    <li>Themes</li>
    <li>Fanfic (neocities only) <img src="https://archiveofourown.org/images/ao3_logos/logo_42.png" alt="AO3 logo" style="object-fit: contain; height: 1em; width: 1em; display: inline-block"></li>
    <li>Character sheet viewer for my dnd characters 🎲</li>
    <li>Github widget/embed</li>
    <li>
      RSS feed viewer (head over to <a
        href="https://afterlifepro.neocities.org/?app=rss">my old neocities</a
      > to use an RSS reader for now)
    </li>
    <li>Serenity OS emojis (waiting on <code style="display: inline">font-variant-emoji</code> to become <a href="https://caniuse.com/?search=font-variant-emoji">baseline supported in most browsers</a>)</li>
    <li class="complete">v1.0.0</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<style>
  .wrapper {
    background-color: #00000020;
    width: calc(100% + 1rem);
    margin-inline: calc(-1 * var(--overflow));
    padding-block: var(--overflow);
  }

  li.complete {
    list-style-type: "✓";
  }
</style>